<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-04T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">625.5131/67: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-04T18:00:00-04:00">February 4, 1936—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>16. Department’s 5, February 1, 2 p.m. In the absence of the
                                Minister,<note n="11" xml:id="d287fn11">Miguel Cruchaga
                                Tocornal.</note> the Undersecretary for Foreign Affairs<note n="12" xml:id="d287fn12">German Vergara Donoso.</note> informs me that <pb facs="0414" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/> the new French-Chilean
                            Commercial Convention has been put into force provisionally but that the
                            French-Chilean <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> of May 22, 1931 will
                            not be denounced until the date of ratification of the new agreement. He
                            added that in any event our <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> of
                            September 28, 1931 will remain in force until the date of formal
                            ratification.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>